cloud-architecture-diagram

title Kubernetes Microservices Platform - YouTube Summarizer - PROJECT 12

// Infrastructure Provisioning
Terraform [icon: terraform, label: "Terraform (IaC)"]

// AWS Infrastructure
AWS Infrastructure [icon: aws-cloud] {
  EKS Cluster [icon: aws-eks, label: "EKS Kubernetes Cluster"]
  ECR Registry [icon: aws-ecr, label: "ECR (Container Registry)"]
  ALB [icon: aws-elb, label: "Application Load Balancer"]
  VPC [icon: aws-vpc, label: "VPC (Networking)"]
  CloudWatch [icon: aws-cloudwatch, label: "CloudWatch (Monitoring)"]
}

// Kubernetes Services
Kubernetes Services [icon: kubernetes] {
  Python Service [icon: python, label: "FastAPI Service (Python)"]
  TypeScript Service [icon: typescript, label: "Hono Service (TypeScript)"]
  HPA [icon: kubernetes, label: "Horizontal Pod Autoscaler"]
}

// External APIs
AI Services [icon: openai, label: "AI Models (OpenAI, Gemini, Groq)"]
YouTube API [icon: youtube, label: "YouTube API"]

// User Interface
User [icon: user, label: "User"]

// Terraform Deployment
Terraform -> AWS Infrastructure: terraform apply

// Container Deployment
ECR Registry -> Kubernetes Services: Container images

// Microservices Flow
User -> ALB: 1. API requests
ALB -> Python Service: 2. Route to FastAPI (features)
ALB -> TypeScript Service: 3. Route to Hono (performance)
Python Service -> YouTube API: 4. Fetch video data
TypeScript Service -> YouTube API: 5. Fetch video data
Python Service -> AI Services: 6. Generate summaries
TypeScript Service -> AI Services: 7. Generate summaries
HPA -> Kubernetes Services: 8. Auto-scale pods
Kubernetes Services -> CloudWatch: 9. Metrics & logs